WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.880
This solution begins by locating the current directory and confirming the active identity. Those two checks prevent us from changing the wrong place as the wrong user.

2
00:00:14.230 --> 00:00:27.310
The inbox contains a welcome note and a draft. We create the required project hierarchy with mkdir -p and brace expansion, so both child directories are made in one predictable command.

3
00:00:27.660 --> 00:00:37.340
cp preserves the welcome source while mv relocates the draft into the archive. The full destination names make the intended final state explicit.

4
00:00:37.690 --> 00:00:46.610
Finally, find proves that both files exist at the expected paths, and cat verifies their contents. The platform checker now evaluates the same observable filesystem state.
